00:02:42.700 --> 00:02:46.280
So why I write is
really quite basic.

00:02:46.280 --> 00:02:48.520
I'm a Zimbabwean-American.

00:02:48.520 --> 00:02:52.360
I am an African woman,
and I was outraged.

00:02:52.360 --> 00:02:54.303
You know, I'm driven by outrage.

00:02:54.303 --> 00:02:57.380
And I was driven by the outrage
that there were so few stories

00:02:57.380 --> 00:02:58.980
that reflected that experience.

00:02:58.980 --> 00:03:00.450
The experience of African women.

00:03:00.450 --> 00:03:02.480
The stories of women
of African origin.

00:03:02.480 --> 00:03:04.830
So that really is
my artistic mandate,

00:03:04.830 --> 00:03:06.600
is to make sure
that these voices--

00:03:06.600 --> 00:03:10.651
these faces are front and center
in whatever I create, anyway.

00:03:10.651 --> 00:03:12.400
So that's really at
the core of everything

00:03:12.400 --> 00:03:15.080
I do and of course
Eclipsed is no exception.

00:03:15.080 --> 00:03:19.770
In terms of the exact story, I
came across an article about,

00:03:19.770 --> 00:03:23.000
actually the liberation
fighters-- well rebel fighters

00:03:23.000 --> 00:03:25.684
as many different
perspectives on what

00:03:25.684 --> 00:03:26.850
they were these ladies were.

00:03:26.850 --> 00:03:28.970
But they were in
the Lord Rebel Army,

00:03:28.970 --> 00:03:31.420
which is one of the rebel
factions that were fighting

00:03:31.420 --> 00:03:32.680
against Charles Taylor.

00:03:32.680 --> 00:03:34.180
And when I came
across this article,

00:03:34.180 --> 00:03:35.700
actually in the
New York Times, it

00:03:35.700 --> 00:03:37.650
was these women who
were just really

00:03:37.650 --> 00:03:39.500
clad in these
really cool clothes,

00:03:39.500 --> 00:03:41.060
and really looked kind of cool.

00:03:41.060 --> 00:03:44.099
They're like early 20s,
and they have these AK-47s

00:03:44.099 --> 00:03:45.140
slung around their backs.

00:03:45.140 --> 00:03:47.030
And I had just never
seen anything like it.

00:03:47.030 --> 00:03:50.020
I grew up in southern
Africa during peace time

00:03:50.020 --> 00:03:51.330
so I had never seen a war.

00:03:51.330 --> 00:03:53.560
I'd never seen the
images of women in war,

00:03:53.560 --> 00:03:56.390
and I knew that was a
story I had to pursue,

00:03:56.390 --> 00:03:58.440
in whichever way,
shape, or form I could.

00:03:58.440 --> 00:04:00.549
And so that's where the
journey really began.

00:04:00.549 --> 00:04:02.840
I only actually started to
pursue it a few years later,

00:04:02.840 --> 00:04:04.450
because I had another
play in between.

00:04:04.450 --> 00:04:08.500
But it became a journey
that I didn't expect.

00:04:08.500 --> 00:04:09.870
I went to Liberia.

00:04:09.870 --> 00:04:14.310
Met women who really
devastated and astounded

00:04:14.310 --> 00:04:16.550
me, and inspired
me, and entrusted me

00:04:16.550 --> 00:04:17.500
with their stories.

00:04:17.500 --> 00:04:20.380
And ultimately, I synthesized
it into this story.

00:04:20.380 --> 00:04:24.430
In terms of what I want, it's
very interesting the idea

00:04:24.430 --> 00:04:25.610
of a message, you know.

00:04:25.610 --> 00:04:29.170
Because as a playwright
I think you're not--

00:04:29.170 --> 00:04:32.070
you can't really
pursue a message.

00:04:32.070 --> 00:04:34.250
You're not a pastor.

00:04:34.250 --> 00:04:36.900
You're not-- you're
a storyteller.

00:04:36.900 --> 00:04:38.610
And all you can
do is really hope

00:04:38.610 --> 00:04:40.760
that the story
connects and relates

00:04:40.760 --> 00:04:43.200
to people in whatever way.

00:04:43.200 --> 00:04:46.340
So I don't know how it will
relate to her versus to him,

00:04:46.340 --> 00:04:48.920
but I hope that at some
point somewhere in there,

00:04:48.920 --> 00:04:52.090
they will lose their
sense of time and place,

00:04:52.090 --> 00:04:55.250
and they will start to feel
a human connection to what's

00:04:55.250 --> 00:04:57.750
happening on the stage and to
the characters that maybe they

00:04:57.750 --> 00:04:59.360
never really ever get to see.

00:04:59.360 --> 00:05:01.380
Which is kind of the
goal of what I write.

00:05:01.380 --> 00:05:04.690
It's really about trying to
give those voices a space.

00:05:04.690 --> 00:05:06.450
So that's the goal really.

00:05:06.450 --> 00:05:09.430
Is to say, is there really
a difference between you

00:05:09.430 --> 00:05:10.722
and any of these women up here?

00:05:10.722 --> 00:05:13.346
You know, because I think that's
what happens to African women.

00:05:13.346 --> 00:05:14.380
We get other otherized.

00:05:14.380 --> 00:05:17.830
We get put in a category of the
other, and those over there,

00:05:17.830 --> 00:05:20.380
and you know, wh-- statistics.

00:05:20.380 --> 00:05:23.870
And so the goal is
really to decimate that,

00:05:23.870 --> 00:05:25.750
and to make it
something where you

00:05:25.750 --> 00:05:28.660
have to walk out
and feel that there

00:05:28.660 --> 00:05:30.680
is no difference between
you in those people.

00:05:30.680 --> 00:05:32.570
They are connected to you.

00:05:32.570 --> 00:05:34.040
It's just geography.

00:05:34.040 --> 00:05:36.800
And if you were in a
situation this dire,

00:05:36.800 --> 00:05:39.060
you could end up,
kind of, probably

00:05:39.060 --> 00:05:42.470
responding in a way that's kind
of similar to one of these five

00:05:42.470 --> 00:05:43.034
women.

00:05:43.034 --> 00:05:44.700
Like, it's the same
as the Walking Dead,

00:05:44.700 --> 00:05:45.540
actually, funnily.

00:05:45.540 --> 00:05:46.410
The premise.

00:05:46.410 --> 00:05:46.910
It is.

00:05:46.910 --> 00:05:50.180
It's who would you be if
the world got this dire?

00:05:50.180 --> 00:05:51.440
You'd be one of them.

00:05:51.440 --> 00:05:53.270
And that's really the goal.

00:05:53.270 --> 00:05:57.170
The humor, yeah it's strategic
because it takes down guards.

00:05:57.170 --> 00:05:59.780
If you're laughing,
you're getting

00:05:59.780 --> 00:06:00.780
more and more connected.

00:06:00.780 --> 00:06:03.640
You're finding yourself
more involved and more--

00:06:03.640 --> 00:06:05.150
more in love with these people.

00:06:05.150 --> 00:06:08.000
And so once again, they
can't be the other anymore.

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:09.130
That really sums it up.

