00:27:05.230 --> 00:27:08.770
And then there's the limitations
that the world puts--

00:27:08.770 --> 00:27:10.370
imposes on you.

00:27:10.370 --> 00:27:14.740
Those limitations really
don't have anything

00:27:14.740 --> 00:27:18.650
to do with the person
you are or can be.

00:27:18.650 --> 00:27:24.640
So, when it comes to Hollywood--
I mean, I grew up in Kenya.

00:27:24.640 --> 00:27:26.540
I had this dream to be an actor.

00:27:26.540 --> 00:27:28.290
I didn't have a plan for it.

00:27:28.290 --> 00:27:30.240
I didn't know how
it could happen.

00:27:30.240 --> 00:27:34.500
But what was instilled
in me was this idea

00:27:34.500 --> 00:27:37.370
that you do your best
exactly where you are.

00:27:37.370 --> 00:27:42.300
Like, you challenge yourself,
you compete with yourself,

00:27:42.300 --> 00:27:45.400
first and foremost, before
you compete with anybody else.

00:27:45.400 --> 00:27:49.180
And when that is the focus,
then you become your own bar,

00:27:49.180 --> 00:27:49.970
you know?

00:27:49.970 --> 00:27:52.130
And that's what you're
chasing, your own bar.

00:27:52.130 --> 00:27:53.760
Not someone else's.

00:27:53.760 --> 00:27:56.280
And I think that's just
the philosophy with which I

00:27:56.280 --> 00:27:58.359
go about living my life.

00:27:58.359 --> 00:27:59.650
FEMALE SPEAKER: Very inspiring.

00:27:59.650 --> 00:28:00.930
