00:29:22.180 --> 00:29:24.890
of what other African
stories are going on,

00:29:24.890 --> 00:29:27.696
and how you've then able
to bring it to Broadway.

00:29:27.696 --> 00:29:29.320
I know it's a long
story but, you know,

00:29:29.320 --> 00:29:30.632
that sort of question.

00:29:30.632 --> 00:29:32.590
DANAI GURIRA: I mean, in
terms of the barriers,

00:29:32.590 --> 00:29:34.950
I mean it's really
beautifully said by Lupita.

00:29:34.950 --> 00:29:37.700
It is that idea that--
the thing that you

00:29:37.700 --> 00:29:41.685
said that was key to me was you
said, and then they tell you.

00:29:41.685 --> 00:29:43.560
And the key thing, which
is what Lupita said,

00:29:43.560 --> 00:29:45.670
is you don't listen
to what they tell you.

00:29:45.670 --> 00:29:47.560
Those are imposed barriers
which have nothing

00:29:47.560 --> 00:29:51.690
to do with who you are
or what your destiny is.

00:29:51.690 --> 00:29:54.040
And I think-- I come across
a lot of young writers

00:29:54.040 --> 00:29:57.580
who come up to me, young African
women, African-American women.

00:29:57.580 --> 00:30:02.260
And that question comes up
about-- but they-- and I just

00:30:02.260 --> 00:30:04.390
read this about this
theater not doing that.

00:30:04.390 --> 00:30:06.910
And I'm like, what does
that have to do with you?

00:30:06.910 --> 00:30:09.960
And it is a counter
way of thinking.

00:30:09.960 --> 00:30:12.680
But it is actually
the way of thinking.

00:30:12.680 --> 00:30:14.740
It is the only way of
thinking because we are,

00:30:14.740 --> 00:30:17.500
and this is what we
have to bear in mind,

00:30:17.500 --> 00:30:20.290
especially when you are,
for instance like you

00:30:20.290 --> 00:30:21.580
and I, African women.

00:30:21.580 --> 00:30:25.140
We are creating brand new paths.

00:30:25.140 --> 00:30:28.140
There is no precedent,
largely and often.

00:30:28.140 --> 00:30:31.040
So if you're looking for people
to tell you whether or not,

00:30:31.040 --> 00:30:33.910
or what, or when, you
can't because they

00:30:33.910 --> 00:30:37.220
don't know, because
there's nothing before you.

00:30:37.220 --> 00:30:39.560
So you actually have
to lead the way.

00:30:39.560 --> 00:30:41.120
And there are going
to be setbacks.

00:30:41.120 --> 00:30:43.580
We had a setback with
this play six years ago

00:30:43.580 --> 00:30:45.370
when it did not
come to New York.

00:30:45.370 --> 00:30:48.510
And I remember lamenting to God.

00:30:48.510 --> 00:30:51.940
And you know what I felt
spiritually, was, just

00:30:51.940 --> 00:30:53.760
write the next one.

00:30:53.760 --> 00:30:55.450
Just write the next one.

00:30:55.450 --> 00:30:56.960
And so I had another
story to tell.

00:30:56.960 --> 00:30:59.240
And I was going to make
sure I got that one told.

00:30:59.240 --> 00:31:01.170
And that's what I did.

00:31:01.170 --> 00:31:03.440
And then this one I
took care of itself.

00:31:03.440 --> 00:31:07.070
Little did we know a
wonderful understudy at Yale

00:31:07.070 --> 00:31:09.800
was going to turn
into an amazing star.

00:31:09.800 --> 00:31:11.800
Thankfully we were
very sweet to her.

00:31:16.110 --> 00:31:17.120
But that's the beauty.

00:31:17.120 --> 00:31:19.694
I mean, that's a beautiful--
that is that astounding story.

00:31:19.694 --> 00:31:21.360
FEMALE SPEAKER: Life
works out that way.

00:31:21.360 --> 00:31:23.720
DANAI GURIRA: We
had done our best

00:31:23.720 --> 00:31:27.020
we had competed with ourselves
we've pursued excellence

00:31:27.020 --> 00:31:30.340
and we put it all out there
myself and Liesl and we knew

00:31:30.340 --> 00:31:33.760
and some of the ladies on this
I must mention Pascal Armand

00:31:33.760 --> 00:31:36.710
and John who were with
us back at Yale also,

00:31:36.710 --> 00:31:39.290
who have held these
characters stunningly together

00:31:39.290 --> 00:31:42.100
for a long-- and kept evolving
them into amazing realms

00:31:42.100 --> 00:31:44.360
right now on the stage
where you see them.

00:31:44.360 --> 00:31:47.220
And so, we did our all.

00:31:47.220 --> 00:31:50.260
And then we-- you trust that
those seeds have been planted.

00:31:50.260 --> 00:31:52.460
And sometimes they're not
going to sprout tomorrow.

00:31:52.460 --> 00:31:54.876
And sometimes they're not going
to sprout for a few years.

00:31:54.876 --> 00:31:57.320
But you keep going on with
your mission, and your destiny,

00:31:57.320 --> 00:31:58.270
and your calling.

00:31:58.270 --> 00:31:59.200
Because you're needed.

00:31:59.200 --> 00:32:00.075
Your voice is needed.

00:32:00.075 --> 00:32:02.600
It doesn't matter if
they don't see it yet.

00:32:02.600 --> 00:32:05.124
The voice is needed and you
cannot listen to the they.

00:32:05.124 --> 00:32:06.540
FEMALE SPEAKER:
That is the truth.

00:32:06.540 --> 00:32:08.970
PASCALE ARMOND: And not
only that but it's doubled.

00:32:08.970 --> 00:32:09.750
It has doubled.

00:32:09.750 --> 00:32:12.600
Because not only is Eclipsed
